&lt;p&gt;Thus we consume much less electricity than usual. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://spectrum.ge/images/Blog/skandinaviuri-3.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;608&quot; height=&quot;403&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Of course, these styles may not match your taste, but at least, you can use the principles and details that make the interior way more efficient.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Some of the recommendations to make your indoor environment more ecologically friendly are:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;+&lt;/strong&gt; Use light colors wall covering&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;+&lt;/strong&gt; Use organic and natural materials&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;+&lt;/strong&gt; Big windows are a &quot;must&quot;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;+&lt;/strong&gt; Use recycled and secondary furnishing&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;+&lt;/strong&gt; Place as many plants as possible.&lt;/p&gt;</content>
